You thought you were always
wrong and acted all cool.

249
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:27,620
You can stop.

250
00:27:27,620 --> 00:27:32,930
Rude and speak harsh words,
but they were all true.

251
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:40,200
Even when unnecessary, you act all
crazy so that a coward like me...

252
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:44,290
can be ashamed, feel
small, feel miserable.

253
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,640
Is that a compliment?

254
00:27:47,910 --> 00:27:48,780
It's a compliment.

255
00:27:57,120 --> 00:28:00,390
What's our relationship? We
must've been very close.

256
00:28:01,260 --> 00:28:05,800
We weren't close. I really hated you.

257
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:10,400
I cursed you saying, "I hope he
disappears from this world."

258
00:28:11,570 --> 00:28:16,040
So... next time...

259
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:19,980
let's meet again.

260
00:28:21,610 --> 00:28:23,850
I'll be really good to you then.

261
00:28:24,510 --> 00:28:26,020
Like a true brother...

262
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:30,420
I'll cherish you...

263
00:28:35,490 --> 00:28:36,630
and will love you.

264
00:28:37,390 --> 00:28:41,060
Forget it. What's the heck?

265
00:29:25,900 --> 00:29:26,610
What's this?

266
00:29:26,710 --> 00:29:29,180
I found it on the street. You keep it.

267
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:34,790
Am I a beggar? Why do you give me
everything you pick up off the streets?

268
00:29:35,790 --> 00:29:38,160
Fine. I bought it.

269
00:29:40,140 --> 00:29:41,290
You can have it.

270
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:48,690
Why do you give me a ring? You
give it to your girlfriend.

271
00:29:48,700 --> 00:29:50,530
You're my girlfriend. What about it?

272
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:55,310
Yes, I like you. Satisfied?

273
00:29:59,590 --> 00:30:01,110
-You must be crazy.
-I am not crazy.

274
00:30:02,650 --> 00:30:04,750
I'm more normal than any other time.

275
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:08,550
I am not in the state of mind to go
along with your nonsense. Get out.

276
00:30:09,750 --> 00:30:12,260
Get out before I pour
dirty water all over you.

277
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:28,470
Crazy jerk!

278
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,510
Are you in your right mind?

279
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:37,410
My child is dying.

280
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:42,850
Can you do this to a mother
whose son is about to die?

281
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,220
When you go to see Jun Young,

282
00:30:47,420 --> 00:30:49,290
make sure you definitely wear that ring.

283
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:55,130
Wear it and be sure to show it
to Jun Young and show off.

284
00:30:58,230 --> 00:31:00,270
What is it that you want
me to show to Jun Young?

285
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:03,640
Punk, are you even called a human being?

286
00:31:05,110 --> 00:31:06,640
Are you even a human
being, you jerk?

287
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:11,450
Jun Young... He asked me to
look after you as a favor.

288
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:18,960
Show Jun Young that ring. Let him know that even
if he won't be around, his mom will be fine.

289
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:23,760
I told him that Uncle Jeong Sik
will be sure to make you happy.

290
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,360
Make him feel secure.

291
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:37,470
I know you feel sorry and guilty,
so you're avoiding Jun Young.

292
00:31:39,850 --> 00:31:42,580
That's why you're not seeing Jun Young.

293
00:31:44,610 --> 00:31:47,280
But you are his mom.

294
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:57,360
As a mom, what's there to
be sorry or feel guilty?

295
00:32:00,470 --> 00:32:04,070
Before it's too late, go see Jun Young.

296
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,250
I will be released soon.

297
00:32:18,420 --> 00:32:22,950
I won't turn out the way you guys want
me to turn out. I feel so bad for you.

298
00:32:23,980 --> 00:32:25,820
As soon as I get out, I'll get revenge.

299
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:29,860
How dare you fight me?
I'll stomp on all of you.

300
00:32:29,870 --> 00:32:33,230
My dad said he'd pay back every
little thing. Especially your dad.

301
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:39,808
If my dad steps up, someone like Choi Hyeon
Joon will never be able to make a comeback.

302
00:32:43,220 --> 00:32:44,512
Why aren't you saying anything?

303
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,140
Why don't you act all high
and mighty and preach to me?

304
00:32:48,150 --> 00:32:50,452
If I told you that I almost did fall for you...

305
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:54,589
Would you believe me?

306
00:32:56,010 --> 00:33:02,697
If this woman became my girlfriend,
my life would be fun and happy.

307
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:11,406
If I told you there was a moment I
felt that way, would you believe me?

308
00:33:12,780 --> 00:33:14,242
You said you will teach me?

309
00:33:14,930 --> 00:33:16,170
I'm totally good at English.

310
00:33:16,180 --> 00:33:18,980
Do you think I asked for a tutor
because I can't speak English?

311
00:33:19,780 --> 00:33:20,682
What I need is...

312
00:33:20,682 --> 00:33:25,253
An essay that is mindful and moving.
Good enough to get into an Ivy League school.

313
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:28,423
You want college entrance examiners will say,
"Oh, my! We should definitely let him in."

314
00:33:28,730 --> 00:33:34,029
Trusted and practical tip.
Isn't that what you need?

315
00:33:37,050 --> 00:33:43,571
I didn't come through a parachute or back door.
I passed your mom's interview with flying colors.

316
00:33:44,580 --> 00:33:50,145
Everyone thinks I'm not a good student
because I'm pretty. But I'm a good student.

317
00:33:50,300 --> 00:33:52,480
On top of that, I can play
couple of musical instruments...

318
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:55,850
on a professional level. I play sports like
athletes and as for essays or speeches...

319
00:33:55,850 --> 00:33:56,830
What are you doing right now?

320
00:33:56,830 --> 00:33:59,254
I want to make a good impression on you.
So, I'm appealing my charm to you.

321
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:02,123
I'll introduce myself again.

322
00:34:02,450 --> 00:34:07,429
I'm beautiful and have a spectacular resume.
Yet in love with Choi Ji Tae alone.

323
00:34:07,770 --> 00:34:12,333
I'm Yoon Jeong Eun who's got tenacity,
endurance, and even loyalty.

324
00:34:28,370 --> 00:34:32,320
That's right. With your power,
you'd be able to avoid it.

325
00:34:34,790 --> 00:34:36,925
But don't avoid it and
pay for what you did.

326
00:34:39,620 --> 00:34:41,129
I will wait for you.

327
00:34:42,270 --> 00:34:43,231
What do you mean?

328
00:34:43,370 --> 00:34:44,880
Let's talk about this then.

329
00:34:44,890 --> 00:34:46,401
I asked what do you mean?

330
00:34:46,710 --> 00:34:49,137
Whether you'll be hopeless forever...

331
00:34:50,810 --> 00:34:56,044
Or if there's a speck of hope in you...

332
00:34:56,660 --> 00:35:00,381
If there is hope, I'll
be right by your side.

333
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,084
I'll visit you again.

334
00:35:05,690 --> 00:35:06,588
Don't come back.

335
00:35:07,180 --> 00:35:10,258
Don't come back not even twice!
Don't come back until I die!

336
00:35:11,650 --> 00:35:16,297
Don't ever appear in front of
my eyes again! I'll kill you!

337
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:34,048
Who are you?

338
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:42,123
What brings you here?

339
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:54,502
Are you here to sell something?

340
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:05,090
Where did Eul go?

341
00:36:05,100 --> 00:36:09,184
Ah... to the market. Did
you come to see Eul?

342
00:36:15,350 --> 00:36:17,792
Wait for her inside.

343
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,473
Then, you can wait here.

344
00:36:33,930 --> 00:36:34,776
Eul...

345
00:36:36,870 --> 00:36:39,247
When is she coming back?

346
00:36:39,590 --> 00:36:41,082
I don't know about that.

347
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:46,020
She tried to make yukgaejang and failed. So she's
making curry rice and went to buy ingredients.

348
00:38:19,820 --> 00:38:22,717
Can you taste this for me?

349
00:38:24,850 --> 00:38:25,486
Yes.

350
00:38:45,790 --> 00:38:46,874
Is it delicious?

351
00:39:01,660 --> 00:39:02,890
Wow. Awesome.

352
00:39:04,170 --> 00:39:05,693
It's really delicious.

353
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:20,108
It tastes exactly just
like my mom's yukgaejang.

354
00:39:54,250 --> 00:39:56,244
What's wrong? Is it not good?

355
00:39:57,180 --> 00:39:59,113
Is there hair in it?

356
00:40:04,350 --> 00:40:06,187
Wait a minute. I'll get you a new one.

357
00:40:28,570 --> 00:40:30,645
I'm sorry for forgetting about you.

358
00:41:38,012 --> 00:41:40,248
You look totally pretty today,
Ms. Sin Young Ok.

359
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:44,318
I went to the hair salon
for my visit to see you.

360
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:49,323
For my visit, Gook Yeong
bought me this outfit, too.

361
00:41:50,290 --> 00:41:53,261
Man Ok bought these earrings for me.

362
00:41:55,900 --> 00:41:59,901
As for this ring... Uncle
Jeong Sik gave it to me.

363
00:42:02,250 --> 00:42:05,172
Your mom accepted his
proposal, Jun Young.

364
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:06,607
Awesome.

365
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:09,310
Congratulations, Mom.

366
00:42:11,145 --> 00:42:16,951
Gook Yeong and Man Ok... I got
two good son and daughter.

367
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:20,588
I'm so fortunate in my old age.

368
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:25,927
I'm such a bad son.

369
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:28,496
Ah, feel so guilty.

370
00:42:32,790 --> 00:42:33,634
No.

371
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:38,172
My Jun Young is a good son, too.

372
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:40,207
Forget it.

373
00:42:41,300 --> 00:42:46,247
They say your duty as a dutiful son is finished
as you act cute up to the age of three.

374
00:42:47,910 --> 00:42:51,786
Our Jun Young always slept well.

375
00:42:52,110 --> 00:42:56,123
You ate well. And you even pooped well.

376
00:42:57,170 --> 00:43:00,394
You didn't cry, you didn't get sick.

377
00:43:02,740 --> 00:43:08,436
You were so happy to see me.
Always smiling.

378
00:43:09,620 --> 00:43:15,476
Ah... now that you say that, you
make me sound like such a great guy.

379
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:19,280
I got it.

380
00:43:21,060 --> 00:43:23,017
Then let's say Jun Young is a good son.

381
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:30,891
Mom.

382
00:43:40,550 --> 00:43:43,004
I hope you didn't think that...

383
00:43:44,410 --> 00:43:46,574
I didn't do my best.

384
00:43:49,280 --> 00:43:50,044
Okay.

385
00:43:51,630 --> 00:43:53,381
I really lived diligently.

386
00:43:56,720 --> 00:44:00,621
Even if I had a chance to live again, I
don't think I can do better than now.

387
00:44:07,930 --> 00:44:10,164
But still, I feel so sorry to you.

388
00:44:12,080 --> 00:44:13,334
I'm sorry, mom.

389
00:44:13,790 --> 00:44:15,436
I'm truly very sorry.

390
00:44:22,890 --> 00:44:25,012
I'll leave my door open.

391
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:28,983
Come by whenever you want to see me.

392
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:36,257
Even when flowers blossom,
I'll think that you came by.

393
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:42,430
Even when the wind blows,
I'll think that you came by.

394
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:49,270
Even when it rains, I'll
think that you came by.

395
00:44:53,070 --> 00:44:54,642
Even when it snows,

396
00:44:56,680 --> 00:44:58,746
I'll think that you just came by.

397
00:45:04,900 --> 00:45:06,554
Thank you, Jun Young.

398
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:12,560
Thank you for being my son.

399
00:45:16,420 --> 00:45:17,498
Me too.

400
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:25,339
Mom, it was such an honor

401
00:45:27,950 --> 00:45:29,543
to have you as my mom.

402
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:25,499
Regarding KJ's problems that were
revealed through the recent tax audit...

403
00:46:26,350 --> 00:46:30,938
As a member of the
management and family of KJ,

404
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:34,074
Chairwoman Lee Eun Soo and I...

405
00:46:35,910 --> 00:46:38,045
We'll step down as of today.

406
00:46:47,240 --> 00:46:51,325
From now on, KJ management will be taken
over by the professional management team.

407
00:46:54,750 --> 00:46:58,810
Former Chairwoman Lee Eun Soo and I, as
biggest KJ shareholders and family members...

408
00:47:05,180 --> 00:47:07,174
There's a big problem, Assemblyman.

409
00:47:07,340 --> 00:47:09,944
An arrest warrant for you
will be issued soon.

410
00:47:10,620 --> 00:47:12,470
-Have you eaten something?
-Assemblyman.

411
00:47:12,480 --> 00:47:14,081
I've been starving since lunchtime.

412
00:47:14,830 --> 00:47:18,652
Find out if there's a restaurant nearby.
A really good yukgaejang restaurant.

413
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:03,030
Hey. You don't think you
are that pretty, right?

414
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:09,403
Jik wanted to see me and
asked for my selfie.

415
00:48:10,340 --> 00:48:12,206
Did you walk your mom out okay?

416
00:48:14,090 --> 00:48:14,808
Yes.

417
00:48:17,180 --> 00:48:20,514
Hey. What are you looking at?
You don't have any picture of us together.

418
00:48:21,140 --> 00:48:24,852
Hey, why don't you ask a top
star like me to take pictures?

419
00:48:25,150 --> 00:48:26,820
If I do, would you?

420
00:48:28,310 --> 00:48:30,758
Wow. How come I am this pretty!

421
00:48:31,010 --> 00:48:34,328
Oh, I look so shiny, I
can't even look at myself.

422
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:39,833
You're the only one who
says I'm not pretty.

423
00:48:40,650 --> 00:48:42,569
I'm so cool looking.

424
00:48:43,280 --> 00:48:45,706
It's such a waste to show you only.

425
00:48:46,690 --> 00:48:49,576
Hey, why are you taking it so suddenly?

426
00:49:03,210 --> 00:49:06,627
You look really tired.

427
00:49:09,450 --> 00:49:10,464
I know.

428
00:49:12,080 --> 00:49:14,234
Today, I really feel very tired.

429
00:49:15,580 --> 00:49:18,790
-Lean on me and sleep.
-If I fall asleep, you'd wake me up again?

430
00:49:18,800 --> 00:49:20,580
I won't wake you up so just sleep.

431
00:49:20,590 --> 00:49:23,243
You'll wake me up again.
To play with you.

432
00:49:23,390 --> 00:49:26,413
I won't wake you up. Sleep well.

433
00:49:34,980 --> 00:49:37,424
-Are you asleep?
-Yes.

434
00:49:37,500 --> 00:49:39,660
How come an asleep
person can even answer?

435
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:44,064
Are you really asleep?

436
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:47,701
No, I'm not.

437
00:49:49,350 --> 00:49:50,904
Am I really not pretty?

438
00:49:51,610 --> 00:49:53,073
You're pretty.

439
00:49:55,560 --> 00:49:57,411
You are so pretty that I
don't even dare look at you.

440
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:13,827
Are you sleeping?

441
00:50:23,700 --> 00:50:25,205
Are you really sleeping?

442
00:50:35,682 --> 00:50:36,750
I got it.

443
00:50:37,570 --> 00:50:39,053
I won't make you talk.

444
00:50:41,590 --> 00:50:43,791
I won't wake you up.

445
00:50:53,710 --> 00:50:59,973
I know. You're tired, it was a long day.

446
00:51:04,090 --> 00:51:05,979
I won't wake you up so.

447
00:51:08,890 --> 00:51:13,020
Forget about your mom.
Forget about your father.

448
00:51:14,250 --> 00:51:15,520
Forget about me too.

449
00:51:18,940 --> 00:51:23,163
Don't worry about anything
else and just sleep.

450
00:51:39,140 --> 00:51:41,348
Thank you, Jun Young.

451
00:51:46,010 --> 00:51:47,488
See you tomorrow.

452
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:46,780
What are you doing not moving boxes?

453
00:52:48,749 --> 00:52:50,800
Oppa, are you going to fool around?

454
00:52:50,810 --> 00:52:54,460
Come here and look at this!
The tree has sprouted!

455
00:52:54,470 --> 00:52:55,455
What are you saying?

456
00:52:55,722 --> 00:53:00,800
This is the tree that Jun Young was going to dig
up saying it's dead. But look, it's sprouting.

457
00:53:00,810 --> 00:53:04,990
Oh, my... you're right. Daebak.

458
00:53:08,830 --> 00:53:09,860
Yes, hello?

459
00:53:09,870 --> 00:53:15,142
Oppa! Oppa, what color do you
like the most red or pink...

460
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:18,712
It's not that. Oppa, what
do you like the most?

461
00:53:19,160 --> 00:53:20,360
I like you, Na Ri.

462
00:53:20,370 --> 00:53:21,800
Whatever.

463
00:53:23,870 --> 00:53:27,850
You know how we're supposed to see
a movie? But something came up...

464
00:53:27,860 --> 00:53:31,460
What do you mean? Then we
can't see a movie today?

465
00:53:31,470 --> 00:53:36,396
No, no, no. Something came up.
So, after we see the movie...

466
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:40,170
I think I have to eat with
you, Gook Yeong oppa.

467
00:53:40,180 --> 00:53:43,670
You really surprised me a lot!

468
00:53:44,137 --> 00:53:45,572
-What is it?
-Hello?

469
00:53:45,950 --> 00:53:47,720
Hello? Oppa?

470
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:49,943
Who is it? Which girl is she?

471
00:53:51,511 --> 00:53:53,490
What girl? What girl?

472
00:53:53,500 --> 00:53:56,483
Why do you call a lady
I'm seeing a girl?

473
00:53:57,080 --> 00:54:01,989
Hey! There's a weird
picture in this camera.

474
00:54:21,990 --> 00:54:23,243
This is Sin Jun Young.

475
00:54:30,830 --> 00:54:35,289
Few months ago, my doctor told me...

476
00:54:36,910 --> 00:54:40,127
that I won't be able
to live much longer.

477
00:54:43,450 --> 00:54:49,102
I was stunned, but all
people die someday.

478
00:55:02,990 --> 00:55:07,020
The thing that I'm most
worried about is...

479
00:55:09,289 --> 00:55:15,796
if I've ever wronged the people I love.

480
00:55:20,710 --> 00:55:23,837
I was sincerely happy.

481
00:55:26,460 --> 00:55:31,745
I've spent warm moments with them.

482
00:55:42,850 --> 00:55:47,394
Perhaps knowing the limits of time...

483
00:55:50,597 --> 00:55:53,100
helps you reveal true
feelings you've been hiding

484
00:55:53,770 --> 00:56:00,380
and give you courage. It may be
the last blessing given to me.

485
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:11,718
As of yesterday,

486
00:56:16,100 --> 00:56:20,093
I passed three-month
mark my doctor told me.

487
00:56:25,480 --> 00:56:31,200
You are watching this
documentary right now.

488
00:56:40,230 --> 00:56:45,419
Am I still... alive?

489
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:55,395
And...

490
00:57:04,171 --> 00:57:08,775
My lover, Eul.

491
00:57:11,011 --> 00:57:14,147
How are you living your life?

492
00:57:33,740 --> 00:57:37,404
CEO! Where is my tape?

493
00:57:37,871 --> 00:57:40,300
I planned on it for over three months.

494
00:57:40,407 --> 00:57:44,444
I protected it even getting paid for it.
Give me the data.

495
00:57:46,460 --> 00:57:48,950
Do you think I came back here to
produce to be treated this way?

496
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:51,284
Hey! Am I doing this for my own good?

